11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 650.12 of Title 21, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. As used in this section, “county employee” means any person
16 employed by a county, including any duly appointed person, or an
17 employee of a firm contracting with a county.
18 B. Any person who, without justifiable or excusable cause,
19 commits any assault, battery, or assault and battery upon the person
20 of a county employee while such employee is in the performance of
21 his or her duties shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor
22 punishable by imprisonment in the county jail for a period not to
23 exceed one (1) year, a fine not to exceed One Thousand Dollars
24 ($1,000.00), or by both such imprisonment and fine.
