1 C. Any person who, without justifiable or excusable cause,
2 commits any aggravated battery or aggravated assault and battery
3 upon the person of a county employee shall, upon conviction, be
4 guilty of a felony punishable by imprisonment in the custody of the
5 Department of Corrections for a term not to exceed two (2) years, a
6 fine not to exceed Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00), or by both
7 such imprisonment and fine.
8 D. Every county site shall post in a prominent place a notice
9 having the following or similar language: “FELONY CHARGES MAY BE
10 FILED AGAINST ANY PERSON(S) COMMITTING AN AGGRAVATED ASSAULT OR
11 BATTERY UPON ANY COUNTY EMPLOYEE.”
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
